review_blob:
Big disappointment. So popular, so hard to obtain, but first impression is its overrated. Sweet on the palette, hard to identify any distigusgished malt flavor. Good viscosity, creamy head.
This is a girly beer. Anyone remember Michigan Sreaming Pumpkin? Anyone try Elysans Night Owl? So many pumpkin beers out today, likely there are many better than this one. 4 words... Not Worth The Price.

Not impressive as a stout.  Tastes like theyre using shucked smoked oyster shells.  That what a garbage can of those MFers smells like anyway.  This isnt a beer for anyone in food service, too close to bad kitchen oder.  Bitter for the claimed IBU.  Just a weird beer.
beer_name: Flying Dog Pearl Necklace Oyster Stout

review_blob: Black as night, nice short dark brown/gray head.  Smells roasty.  Great body, nice viscosity for a stout.  Tastes of roasted malts and toasted oatmeal.  Great beer.

Smells sweet.  Beautifully clear and golden.  Nicely carbonated, very low head retention.  First sip is interesting, a big mess of flavors.  Lots of unfermented sweetness, which reminds me too much of home-brewed beer made with old malt extract.  I could have enjoyed a small glass of this one, the sweetness makes it difficult to come back to.
Nice but subtle flavors.  Not very aggressively hopped for a double IPA.  No head retention, very light oak flavor, you have to look for it to know its there.
Deceiving dark malt lacks any roastiness or body.  Nice head, no flavor.  Dry through and through.  Needs more complexity.
Nice sour!  Really nice brown gold color, perfect body for the style.  Taste is mildly sour first, and finishes dry sour.  Enjoyable like a lambic, or other soured Belgian.
beer_name: Uinta Crooked Line Birthday Suit: 20th Anniversary

review_blob: Nice change from Insanity, Weyerbachers other bourbon barreled offering. Little hop aroma or flavor.  Strong but smooth bourbon flavor element.  A little boozy on the finish.  Black as night malt base lacks a little viscosity most of these barrel beers have.
Nice upfront fruity hoppiness, nice gentle carbonation.  Like Don Ho says, tiny bubbles make me happy.  This is nothing like I thought a threaded 60 min and 90 min would be like, a whole new animal.
Nice hoppy intro.  Feels like a response to all the fresh hoppy 2xipa on tap this time of year.  Light malt, not sweet not dry.  Hops suggest grapefruit, citrus, with a bitter bite at the end.
Tastes like a band-aid smells.  Has a very medicine taste, yuck.  Notes of vanilla and adhesive.  Nice amber color, little lacing, no head retention.  I doubt this will improve with age.

Seemingly bitter from the roasted malts, but the perceivable IBUs are pretty high too.  Nice thick malt base, glues its balance to your tongue.  You know those beers that either help you work out problems or get someone pregnant?  This is one.  Thank you Flying Dog.
Lots of bananas and other fruit.  A less hoppy version of Yeti if memory serves, and I like that.  This bottle came from my cellar, had a few months to mellow.  I would certainly seek it out again.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Belgian Style

review_blob: Great ale, thick on the palate.  Distinctly different kinds of sweet, but still not too sweet.  Perfect to toast in the new year.
Smells funny.  A little fruity and hop bitter up front.  Finishes dry and warm, like red wine.  Tasty.
Very bitter hops.  I love barley wine, and Flying Mouflan is typical in its well defined uncorrupted hop and malt flavors, but this isnt my favorite.  Finishes smoother than it starts.
Excellent!  Rating/drinking this one fresh, but some will go into the cellar for sure.  Clean flavors from the malt and a distinct but not overpowering hoppiness from the finish.  Warming and earthy.
This is disgusting.  Too many smoked malts, no maple sweetness, no saltiness from the bacon.   Tastes of phony liquid smoke chemicals.  Yuck.
beer_name: Rogue Voodoo Doughnut Bacon Maple Ale

review_blob: Pours like lava, tastes a little like fire... Poured from the bottle slow, almost heavy.  I enjoyed the spice and citrus, but too much hop lingering after.  Santa can keep it next year.
Thick creamy body, slight coffee smell.  Tastes like a good milk stout, with a nice coffee finish.  Doesnt knock me over, but a decent brew.

Very drinkable, the balance of hop and malt is just right.  Founders brews always have such a nice complex smell and body.  Reds finish is crisp, leaving a slight bitterness and hoppy aroma in my mouth.
Smells great, not very thick or clingy for a stout.  There wasnt anything to hold all that delicious blueberry I was smelling, on the tongue.  A nice mocha after flavor.
